  "firstAcquaintance": "A hound-kin girl taken in by a kind undead. She is studying hard to become an excellent maid.",
  "personality": "Innocent, kind, and optimistic. She can befriend anyone.",
  "like": "Femur bones",
  "familiarData": "Amel was abandoned in the forest at birth and picked up by an undead. Initially, the undead planned to raise her into a slave who would accept the undead tribe, but gradually came to care for her as a daughter.\nHowever, word spread that this undead treated demi-humans kindly, and the leader believed this would undermine the slave hierarchy. Ultimately, Amel had to set out wandering alone.\nIn the forest, Amel - having grown up surrounded by kind care - helped injured magical beasts and spent months living with them, but was eventually captured by slave hunters.\nFrom her experiences, it's clear that Amel possesses remarkable good luck. Even with her innocent and naive personality, she manages to live carefree.",
